modStarterQuestWelcome:
{#--color-brown:If you're new to Wayward, this {/Starter Quest/} can help you survive by teaching you the basics. This optional walkthrough will take approximately 20-40 minutes.}

Press {BINDINGS:DialogQuests} to toggle this dialog.

Click "{/Complete Quest/}" to start the quest line.

modStarterQuestGearUp:
{#--color-brown:Attacking creatures will use items in your inventory when equipped to your main hand. Let's equip an item now.}

1. Open your equipment {(HELP/INTERFACE):dialog} with {BINDINGS:DialogEquipment} or click the equipment icon at the top of the screen.

2. Equip a tool or weapon by dragging it from your inventory to the equipment slot of your choice.

Alternatively, you can {BINDINGS:GameItemEquipToggle} to toggle it equipped or not.

{(HELP/HELD_ITEMS):Learn more about Held Items}

modStarterQuestActionSlots:
{#--color-brown:All items have a list of actions that can be performed on them at any time.}

{BINDINGS:GameItemMenu} to open an item's action menu.

{#--color-brown:Using actions in this way can be cumbersome. To bind an item's action to a single keypress, you can use the action bar.}

- Drag and drop an item into an action slot.

- OR use one of the "Assign Action" bindings. While hovering over an item, use {BINDINGS:GameActionBarAssignSlot0}, {BINDINGS:GameActionBarAssignSlot1}, or {BINDINGS:GameActionBarAssignSlot2} for example to use slot 1/2/3.

{#--color-brown:Once the item is in the action slot, it can be used with its corresponding bind (shown when hovering over an action slot).}



Additionally or alternatively, you can bind specific actions to an action slot by using {BINDINGS:MenuContextMenu} on an empty action slot to assign any action. These actions will automatically use the best item for that action in your inventory if applicable.
